This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category because it discusses access controls, which are a fundamental aspect of security. It could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) because access controls are an important aspect of software design. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) because access controls are important in distributed systems. It could also be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) because access controls are important in database management. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) because access controls are often implemented through programming languages.
